rComments: One of the best profs at UT Law. Very down to earth and approachable.
Excellent prof! The course material is very clear, his lectures very organized and crystal clear.

Very intelligent.  Goes above and beyond to help students out.  Does tend to go a little overlong in answering questions and doesn't control class discussion as well as he could.  Great prof.  Also very interested and involved in student life.

Very nice and relaxed professor. He does tend to get caught up in his explanations that can go on forever. I am distracted by the urge to take him shopping for clothes that fit. Every plaid shirt and pair of kakis are about 2 sizes too big.
Thinks he's a bit too clever. Brings the ideological humour around a bit too predictably.  Nice guy, very clear, but you'll be bored by mid-October.
Very clear, goes straight through the case book.  Adds problems and discusses the solutions which really helps in understanding the concepts.  Great sense fo humour.  Favours plaid shirts.
